“The world is your oyster” they said! On the weekends you can find me and Captain Jack tending to our oyster farm. Those of you not familiar with oysters will be surprised to know that each oyster filters 50 gallons of water each day purifying and cleaning our water ways. That’s why the type of farming we do is called “Regenerative Aquaculture”. We have big plans for adding other regenerative and net positive crops like kelp as well as employing renewable business practices like charging our batteries through solar. More to come and watch this space! 🌊 🦪 ♻️
